New Records: Ayoub El Kaabi completed his hat-trick with a stunning header, bringing the score to 5-0
Key Match Events: Azzedine Ounahi took full advantage of poor marking by the Congolese defense to score the evening’s opening goal just eight minutes into the match
Chadi Riad capitalized on another defensive error to score Morocco’s second goal
Ayoub El Kaabi scored his second goal of the match in the 39th minute, this time assisted by Ounahi
Soufiane Rahimi added to Congo’s misery by scoring the sixth goal of the night, with Brahim providing the assist
Post-Match Reflections: Ayoub El Kaabi stood out as the player of the match with three goals and an assist

Should El Kaabi, whether playing alongside or in replacement of En-Nesyri, maintain the momentum and form he has rediscovered in the Greek league, Morocco may be on the verge of hitting the attacking formula that has eluded them for decades
Miscellaneous Highlights: Congo’s defense seemed unable to cope with Morocco’s relentless attack, and their frustration became evident with a series of fouls, resulting in three yellow cards
The Congolese defense was left in shambles for the remainder of the game, unable to contain the Moroccan forwards
Others: The match was played at the Agadir Stadium
